job_description:
The Professional Development and Standards (PDS) Division in ECDA develops Early Childhood (EC) and Early Intervention (EI) professionals and supports preschools to deliver holistic and inclusive care and education through setting quality standards and fostering a culture of continuous learning and innovation.

The Professional Standards and Training (PST) Branch within PDS drives the strategic thrust on developing early childhood professionals effectively. The scope of the PST Branch encompasses:
•	Setting standards for EC professional qualification programmes and work with training providers to ensure quality of programmes;
•	Certifying EC educators to ensure that they meet the relevant professional requirements to work in the sector;
•	Working with training partners to support developing skills and competencies of EC and EI  professionals through CPD courses;
•	Supporting leadership development for the EC sector

The Municipal Services Office (MSO) was set up in Oct 2014 to improve the coordination, delivery and quality of municipal services by Government and Town Councils. These services include the upkeep and improvement of common areas in public and private estates, and the upgrading or provision of facilities and infrastructure.

The next bound of municipal service delivery involves:
i.	ramping up of forward intelligence capabilities to enable foresight planning and support the development of pre-emptive operations;
ii.	deploying data focused tools (e.g. dashboards and regular data reports) to increase the productivity of officers across the municipal sector and to support them in making data-driven policy decisions;
iii.	humanising the digitalisation of government services (e.g. OneService Chatbot) for an optimised, resident-centric experience.

The Trade and International Economic Relations (TIER) cluster drives the formulation of Singapore's foreign economic policy and advances Singapore's economic interests in the international economic arena.

MTI’s International Trade Division (ITD) is charged with protecting and advancing Singapore’s economic interests by:

* Supporting free trade and open markets;
* Upholding and strengthening the rules-based multilateral trading system as embodied in the World Trade Organisation (WTO);
* Deepening economic integration with like-minded countries through free trade agreements (FTA) and bilateral investment treaties (BIT);
* Driving initiatives in regional economic fora such as the Asia-Pacific Economic Cooperation (APEC); and
* Advancing our companies’ interests abroad rigorously, including by lowering barriers for Singapore exports

SSG is a dynamic and forward-thinking organization dedicated to empowering individuals and shaping the future of Singapore's workforce. As the National Skills Authority, SSG leads the charge in driving the SkillsFuture movement, a national initiative that promotes lifelong learning and skills development. With a strong focus on innovation and collaboration, SSG works closely with employers, training providers, and individuals to create a vibrant ecosystem of learning and growth. By offering a wide range of initiatives, programs, and funding schemes, SSG enables individuals to unlock their full potential, acquire new competencies, and stay ahead in a rapidly changing job market. 

The National Jobs-Skills Data Office, under the Skills Intelligence and Planning Division, serves three core functions:
•	Data and Algorithms Innovation and R&D:  Undertake development of new data models and algorithms to serve whole of government’s jobs-skills intelligence needs; 
•	Jobs-Skills Product Management, Development and Delivery: Manage and enhance jobs-skills products, which includes UX/UI design and end-to-end product life cycle management;
•	Data Management and Operations: Centrally manage data quality, data models and data infrastructure to support internal and external users

Come join this game-changing team in SSG, where we empower employers, citizens, training providers, and policymakers to make informed decisions by using a user-centered approach, providing trusted source of jobs-skills data and insights, and a common set of jobs-skills taxonomies for a skills-first future!
